    "biography": "<p>The Mujina haunts regions where humans dwell, its natural form a chilling mimicry of humanity—featureless, with a smooth, egg-like face devoid of eyes, nose, ears, or mouth. A magical creation born to torment mankind, it crafts illusions to don any visage, often posing as an unassuming human until the moment it strikes.</p><p>Possessing uncanny strength, it wields two-handed weapons—save lances, pole arms, or crossbows—in each hand with equal prowess, dealing [[/r 1d6 #Weapon damage]] or more by type. Its blank face, revealed at will, terrifies foes: those of 5 HD or less flee for [[/r 1d3 #Rounds of fear]] at triple speed, while stronger beings must save vs. wands or join them in panic.</p><p>Cunning and hateful, the Mujina infiltrates adventurer bands as a loyal retainer, biding its time before robbing them blind and vanishing. Appearing in groups of [[/r 1d4 #Mujinas wandering]] or [[/r 1d4 #Mujinas in lair]], it speaks Common, its own tongue, and Chaotic, its loathing for human individuality driving its treachery.</p><p><strong>Terrain:</strong> Any, where humans are found</p>",
